Predictive optimization.

On unity catalog managed tables, predictive optimization runs optimize and vacuum for you, on a schedule that's informed by your actual access patterns. You enable it at the catalog or schema level, and databricks does the right amount of compaction and cleanup, billed at a serverless rate.

There are two reasons this matters at the associate level. First, it's the correct answer whenever a question asks how to keep curated tables performant without writing your own maintenance job.

And second, it is unity catalog only. External tables stored in raw paths outside the catalog do not get this. So it's yet another reason to prefer managed tables.
